Deaths/yr:   1.5M
Vaccine:     No
Discovered:  1922

Disease:     Malaria
Type:        Parasitic
Pathogen:    Plasmodium falciparum
Transmission:Mosquito bite
Symptoms:    Fever, chills, sweating cycles
Treatment:   Artemisinin combination therapy
Deaths/yr:   0.619M
Vaccine:     Yes (RTS,S approved 2021)
Discovered:  1880

Disease:     Dengue
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Dengue virus
Transmission:Aedes mosquito
Symptoms:    Fever, severe joint pain, rash
Treatment:   Supportive care, fluids
Deaths/yr:   0.04M
Vaccine:     Yes (for previously infected)
Discovered:  1779

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    GDP
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Total value of all goods and services produced in a country annually
Formula:    GDP = C + I + G + (X-M)
Economist:  Simon Kuznets
Example:    USA GDP 2023: $27.4 trillion; China: $17.9 trillion

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

Concept:    Central Bank
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government institution managing currency, money supply, interest rates
Formula:    Taylor Rule for interest rates
Economist:  John Taylor
Example:    US Federal Reserve raised rates to 5.25% in 2023 to fight inflation

